{
  "texts": [
    "Once patient histories and embeddings have been created, it is possible to create multiple disease models quickly using the same methodology, reducing the burden on clinician time required for development.",
    "Transfer learning from pre-trained embeddings can also improve performance, especially where limited data is available.",
    "The calculation of SHAP values can provide clinicians with a means of evaluating the features that are contributing to the models' predictions.",
    "This approach was developed using common python packages and cloud services-technologies which are within the reach of healthcare systems today.",
    "The approach presented here is a promising methodology for increasing the precision with which PHM practitioners can identify at-risk patients and take preventative steps to improve their health outcomes."
  ]
}